Program: Omnibus
Title: Incarceration of Japanese Americans during WWII
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376mbx
Last Broadcast Date: 10 January 2002
'The roots lie in American racism'. A look at the wartime detention of 120,000 Japanese Americans during WWII. Former detainees and their children recall the period of imprisonment and the consequences of Pearl Harbour.